answers.answer: No, that is not normal. Do you have hepatitis C. If you do it is very common to have elevated liver enzymes.If you don't, you need to find out what is causing the elevated enzymes. You will need to go to the doctor and run tests to find out why your liver is behaving this way.
You can discuss screening for viral hepatitis with your doctor; he'll advise if he feels this is warranted. Good luck--Bill
